  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Betahistine may provide benefit by enhancement of Cerebral Blood Flow (CBF). This
      placebo-controlled pharmacodynamic treatment study will primarily explore the effect of
      betahistine on cerebral blood flow measured by dynamic contrast-enhanced MRI imaging, in a
      patient population with MRI evidence of cerebrovascular compromise. Also it will be measured
      if CBF changes correlate with gait and cognitive changes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
